# 🔨 AgentID — Complete Step-by-Step Build Guide

> This guide takes you from the current state (frontend prototype with mock data) to a fully functional on-chain KYA protocol on Solana mainnet. Every step has exact commands, which tool to use, and what the output should look like.
>
> **📅 Last updated: March 9, 2026** — Phases 1, 2, 3 are **complete**. Program live on devnet: `Gv35udP7tnnVcNiCMLKYeyjx1rfkeos4e6cXsFGr4tcF`

---

## Phase 0: Quick Wins — UI Polish via Lovable  
**⏱️ 1–2 days | 🟣 Tool: Lovable**

These can be done immediately in parallel with everything else. Push to the `exactly-as-seen` repo.

### Step 0.1 — Build the /docs Page

Open Lovable → Prompt:
```
Create a /docs page for the AgentID developer documentation. Include:
- A left sidebar with sections: "Quick Start", "Register Agent", "Verify Agent", 
  "Reputation Score", "CPI Integration", "ELIZA Plugin", "TypeScript SDK", "India Compliance"
- Each section has a title, description paragraph, and a syntax-highlighted code block
- For "Quick Start" show: npm install @agentid/sdk, then a 5-line TypeScript example
- For "CPI Integration" show a Rust code block with verify_agent CPI call
- For "ELIZA Plugin" show: import { agentIdPlugin } from '@agentid/eliza-plugin'
- Match the existing editorial dark theme with serif italic headers and monospace code
- Add the route to App.tsx as /docs
```

### Step 0.2 — Add Analytics Charts to Dashboard

```
Add a recharts analytics section to the Dashboard page, above the agent list.
Show 3 charts side by side:
1. Line chart: "Reputation Over Time" (last 30 days, mock data points)
2. Bar chart: "Daily Transactions" (last 14 days)  
3. Area chart: "USDC Volume" (last 30 days)
Use the green/blue/purple accent colors from the theme.
Keep the charts compact (200px height). Use the same editorial styling.
```

### Step 0.3 — Add Search & Filter to Agents Page

```
Update the Agents page (/agents) to include:
- A search bar at the top that filters agents by name in real-time
- A row of filter pills: "All", "ELIZA", "AutoGen", "CrewAI", "LangGraph", "Custom"
- A sort dropdown: "Reputation (High→Low)", "Reputation (Low→High)", "Recently Active", "Recently Registered"
- When no results match, show a "No agents found" empty state
```

### Step 0.4 — Loading Skeletons

```
Add skeleton loading states to:
- AgentProfile page (skeleton for gauge, info rows, activity feed)
- Dashboard page (skeleton for stats, agent list, treasury)
- Agents page (skeleton for agent rows)
Use animated pulse rectangles matching the border/background colors.
Show skeletons for 1.5 seconds then reveal real content.
```

### Step 0.5 — Onboarding Modal

```
Create a first-visit onboarding modal that appears when users land on the home page 
for the first time (use localStorage to track). 3 animated steps:
1. "What is AgentID?" — brief explainer with the Zap icon
2. "How it works" — 3 bullet points: Register → Build Reputation → Transact
3. "Get Started" — CTA button to /register
Use framer-motion for slide transitions. Dismiss on click-outside or X button.
```

