## Phase 4: Metaplex cNFT Credential  
**⏱️ 2–3 days | 🔵 Codex + 🟢 Antigravity**

### Step 4.1 — Install Metaplex Dependencies

```bash
# In the Anchor program
cargo add mpl-bubblegum spl-account-compression

# In the frontend
npm install @metaplex-foundation/umi @metaplex-foundation/umi-bundle-defaults @metaplex-foundation/mpl-bubblegum
```

### Step 4.2 — Create Merkle Tree

Ask Codex:
```
Write a TypeScript script that creates a Bubblegum Merkle tree on Solana devnet 
for storing compressed NFTs. Max depth 14, max buffer size 64 (supports ~16k NFTs).
Use @metaplex-foundation/umi. Save the tree address to a .env file.
```

### Step 4.3 — Add CPI to Register Instruction

Ask Codex:
```
Update the register_agent instruction to include a CPI call to 
mpl_bubblegum::cpi::mint_v1() after creating the AgentIdentity account.
The cNFT metadata should include:
- name: "AgentID: {agent_name}"
- uri: "https://api.agentid.xyz/metadata/{agent_id_hex}"
- attributes: framework, model, owner, registered_at
- non_transferable: true (soul-bound)
Store the resulting Pubkey in identity.credential_nft
```

### Step 4.4 — Build Metadata API

Ask Codex:
```
Create a simple Express.js API at /api/metadata/:agentId that returns 
Metaplex-compatible JSON metadata for the cNFT:
{
  "name": "AgentID: TradingBot-Alpha",
  "description": "On-chain identity credential for AI agent",
  "image": "https://agentid.xyz/nft/{agentId}.png",
  "attributes": [...]
}
Deploy as a Vercel serverless function.
```

### Step 4.5 — Update Frontend

Ask Antigravity:
```
Update AgentProfile.tsx to display the real cNFT credential:
- Show the cNFT address with a link to Solana Explorer
- Add a "View NFT" button
- Show the Metaplex metadata attributes
```

