## Phase 8: Payment Layer (x402 + Treasury)  
**⏱️ 3–5 days | 🔵 Codex + 🟢 Antigravity**

### Step 8.1 — AgentTreasury Account

Ask Codex:
```
Add an AgentTreasury account to the Anchor program:
- agent_id: [u8; 32]
- usdc_balance: u64
- total_earned: u64, total_spent: u64
- spending_limit_per_tx: u64
- spending_limit_per_day: u64
- spent_today: u64
- day_reset_timestamp: i64
- emergency_pause: bool
- multisig_required_above: u64
- bump: u8

Instructions:
- initialize_treasury: creates treasury PDA for an agent
- autonomous_payment: transfers USDC with safety checks (pause, limits, reputation)
- update_spending_limits: owner-only limit updates
- emergency_pause: owner-only toggle
- deposit: receive USDC into treasury
```

### Step 8.2 — x402 Payment Middleware

Ask Codex:
```
Create an Express middleware using the x402 protocol:
- Agents can gate their API endpoints behind USDC micropayments
- When a request comes in without x402 payment header, return 402 with payment details
- When payment is verified, forward to the agent's handler
- Log the payment as an on-chain AgentAction
Use @coinbase/x402 or implement the spec manually.
```

### Step 8.3 — Wire Dashboard Treasury

Ask Antigravity:
```
Update Dashboard.tsx:
- Read real USDC balance from the AgentTreasury PDA
- Wire spending limit sliders to call update_spending_limits instruction
- Wire emergency pause button to call emergency_pause instruction
- Add a "Deposit USDC" button that transfers USDC to the treasury
- Show real total_earned, total_spent, spent_today values
```

