## Phase 10: Launch & Go-to-Market  
**⏱️ 1 week | Manual**

### Step 10.1 — Onboard First Agents

1. Register 5 test agents on mainnet yourself (different frameworks)
2. Contact 3 Indian AI freelance agencies — offer free KYB verification
3. Help them register their agents and set up TDS compliance

### Step 10.2 — Community Launch

1. Post in ai16z Discord: *"We built an AgentID plugin for ELIZA — your agent now has an on-chain passport"*
2. Post on ELIZA GitHub Discussions
3. Tweet from AgentID account with demo video

### Step 10.3 — DeFi Integration

1. Contact Jupiter/Kamino/Raydium teams
2. Show them the one-line CPI call: `agentid::cpi::verify_agent()`
3. Offer to build the integration PR for them

### Step 10.4 — Blog Post

Write: *"Your AI agent is operating on Solana without an identity. Here's why that's a problem — and how to fix it in 2 lines of code."*

Publish on: Mirror, Medium, dev.to, and Superteam blog.

### Step 10.5 — Grant Submission

1. Submit Milestone 1 proof: GitHub repo + devnet demo + 5 registered agents
2. Submit Milestone 2 proof: npm package + 50 downloads + live reputation
3. Submit Milestone 3 proof: DeFi integration PR + India compliance demo

